<br>
Tell me why, give me information!<br>
<br>
Stuff like that I love to read about.  I'm not posting to be sarcastic, which I know some Xevboard regulars will take this as.  I am not trying to stir up a poopstorm-- I am posting so as to REALLY UNDERSTAND what is generally accepted as common courtesy for specific events.  Abbreviations about specific mobs I've never seen or heard much about mean little to me also BTW. So where applicable I need to know the actual zone name (at least once in the post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) or mob name.<br>
<br>
I'd really like it if we refrained from saying &quot;One time GUILD X did this to uss, the A**holes&quot; and stuff like that.  I posted here, in General, for a reason.  I've read your childish he-said-she-said-guild-bashing-posts in rant for a year and a half. Old news, let it go.  However, help the next generation (me and my friends) to not make those same mistakes. <br>
I've been playing the game for over two years, and not an evening goes by that I don't learn something NEW about EQ, it's content, it's lore, and it's players.  My hope is that this post can help to inform me, and others, of what to do and more importantly what NOT to do.<br>
<br>
