<br>
Generally, Statue is killed fairly early as most guilds who can kill Vind can kill Statue.  Now, Avatar of War is a really high priority target for any raiding guild - a quick look at his loot will tell you why.  It includes, among other things, a very nice agro weapon.  Because of that, it is considered bad form to fail on him and allow him to despawn.  However, Idol and AoW are almost the same mob - Idol hits about the same and is just as fast.  Chances are if you can kill Idol you can kill AoW.  However, if you slow Idol (AoW cannot be slowed) you ruin that parrallel.  So it is considered good form not to slow Idol on your first attempts.  As a matter of fact, most guilds that can kill AoW don't bother to slow Idol anyway - its good practice.<br>
<br>
As for the VT rotation, best you wait until you get there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  The exact details are worked out between the guild leaders.  Currently it guarentees VT (all spawns) to one guild for 2 days after full respawn (simplified version).  It is a rotation because each guild in the cycle gets a turn, then they start over at the first guild.  This is because while VT can be cleared in 6-10 hours, it is not terribly fun to do so.<br>
<br>
Other unwritten rules - if you start a cycle spawn (AoW for example, there are 3 mobs in the cycle, AoW, Idol, and Statue) the entire cycle is yours until you give up or wipe (note that while this seems like common sense it is not in the PnP policy).  Some examples of this are AoW, Arch Lich in Ssraa, and Cursed in Ssraa.<br>
<br>
Another deals with NToV - if your guild kills Airy (can't remember the actual name of the beast <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), your guild is given 2 or 3 days in NToV - can't remember which.  This rule is because NToV is generally really difficult to clear the first couple of times.<br>
<br>
There are probably others.  I know that several guilds work together on backflags (ie - if a guild has extra flags and your guild has completed an encounter, you are allowed to tag along for flag).  This is more of an agreement between specific guilds, not all guilds participate in this.  It is also considered polite to inform people when you are starting the Rallos Zek event in tactics - as if you fail you will kill everyone in the zone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
You'll find that even though high end guilds will race for a spawn and complain if they get beat, they generally are quite civil to each other.<br>
